\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Exercise 14.2 Show that if 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(e_{t},\mathscr{F}_{t}\right)$
\end_inset

 is a MDS and 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{t}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathscr{F}_{t}$
\end_inset

-measurable then 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{t}=X_{t-1}e_{t}$
\end_inset

 is a MDS.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Solution*

\series bold
14.2
\end_layout

\begin_layout Solution*
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{t}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathscr{F}_{t}$
\end_inset

-measurable, we have 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{t}$
\end_inset

 adapted to 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathscr{F}_{t}$
\end_inset

 in that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
E\left[u_{t}\mid\mathscr{F}_{t}\right]=E\left[X_{t-1}e_{t}\mid\mathscr{F}_{t}\right]=X_{t-1}e_{t}.
\]

\end_inset

as 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{t-1}$
\end_inset

is 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathscr{F}_{t}$
\end_inset

 measurable.
 Moreover, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
E\left[u_{t}\mid\mathscr{F}_{t-1}\right]=E\left[X_{t-1}e_{t}\mid\mathscr{F}_{t-1}\right]=X_{t-1}E\left[e_{t}\mid\mathscr{F}_{t-1}\right]=0
\]

\end_inset

We thus have verified 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{t}=X_{t-1}e_{t}$
\end_inset

 being a MDS.
\end_layout

